About the film: Two gangsters, Vincent Vega and Jules Winfield spend their time in philosophical conversations in between showdowns and &quot;solving problems&quot; with the debtor of his crime boss Marsellus Wallace. In parallel, three stories unfold.

The first of them, Vincent looks after his wife Mia and Marsellus rescues her from a drug overdose. The second tells of Butch Coolidge, a boxer, hired Wallace to give in, but deceived him. The third story combines the first two - in a cafe a couple of unfortunate young robbers - Pumpkin and Honey Bath robbery attempt, but Jules stops them.

The lives of two mob hit men, a boxer, a gangster's wife, and a pair of diner bandits intertwine in four tales of violence and redemption.

